What is the primary goal of the PROMIS WOMAN Education Program research study?
A) To increase physical activity among Muslim American women; 
B) To improve dietary habits in the Muslim American community; 
C) To enhance cervical cancer prevention methods tailored to the religious and cultural needs of Muslim American women; 
D) To study the effects of sleep patterns on health outcomes in Muslim American women.

Correct answer: C

If you decide not to participate in the PROMIS WOMAN Education Program, what alternative options are available for cervical cancer prevention education?
A) You will be provided with a standard cervical cancer prevention pamphlet; 
B) There are no alternative educational programs offered; 
C) You will be enrolled in a general health education program not specific to cervical cancer; 
D) You will receive one-on-one counseling sessions with a healthcare provider.

Correct answer: A
